Definitions to common functions & commands.


CREATE TABLE
Need to specify table name and column specifications (data type)

PRIMARY KEY 
Counter automatically increases by 1 with each new imput ie: 1,2,3,...

VARCHAR(20)
stands for "varying width character" used to define a string variable with unknown variable length

NVARCHAR(20)
Similar to VARCHAR(20) but can also allow unique characters from other languages.

Variable NULL
When declaring a variable, NULL states that there may be an empty value.

ALTER TABLE
Add or remove columns, constraints, keys.

DROP TABLE
Used to permanently delete the entire table from the database. 

DELETE TABLE
Used to get rid of specific data in a table. 

